WEBVTT	#Elemental Media Engine(TM) 2.17.0.0

00:00:00.00 --> 00:00:04.01


00:00:04.01 --> 00:00:06.47
Bisa Butler's work has a way of stopping people

00:00:06.47 --> 00:00:07.55
in their tracks.

00:00:07.55 --> 00:00:08.48
Amazing right?

00:00:08.48 --> 00:00:09.38
Oh, my gosh.

00:00:09.38 --> 00:00:11.18
Her life size portraits look like they're

00:00:11.18 --> 00:00:14.10
from the strokes of a painter's brush.

00:00:14.10 --> 00:00:17.64
But Butler is a quilt maker, weaving fabrics of all kinds

00:00:17.64 --> 00:00:20.71
into celebrations of Black life in America.

00:00:20.71 --> 00:00:23.34
I always want my portraits to be life sized,

00:00:23.34 --> 00:00:26.40
to look the person in the eye and to grab them.

00:00:26.40 --> 00:00:29.58
Like despite whatever it is you think of me,

00:00:29.58 --> 00:00:32.04
you're going to recognize me as a human being.

00:00:32.04 --> 00:00:35.16
Butler says she is often inspired by historical photos

00:00:35.16 --> 00:00:39.06
like this one in 1940, a North Carolina family fleeing the Jim

00:00:39.06 --> 00:00:39.99
Crow South.

00:00:39.99 --> 00:00:43.92
In seven months she transformed their story onto fabric.

00:00:43.92 --> 00:00:46.35
What about this photo jumped out at you?

00:00:46.35 --> 00:00:51.96
What jumped out at me was that this family was so unified

00:00:51.96 --> 00:00:58.33
in coming so far and that they were seeking better.

00:00:58.33 --> 00:01:00.49
She learned to sew from her mother and grandmother

00:01:00.49 --> 00:01:02.83
and started out as a school art teacher.

00:01:02.83 --> 00:01:05.92
Now her work graces major magazine covers.

00:01:05.92 --> 00:01:08.14
Last year she had her first solo show

00:01:08.14 --> 00:01:10.27
at the famed Art Institute of Chicago.

00:01:10.27 --> 00:01:12.64
I love the hair, the hair on these.

00:01:12.64 --> 00:01:16.12
Does it feel like you're filling in a gap in history that

00:01:16.12 --> 00:01:17.71
was just left out?

00:01:17.71 --> 00:01:18.93
Absolutely.

00:01:18.93 --> 00:01:19.60
Absolutely.

00:01:19.60 --> 00:01:21.85
I feel like our history has often

00:01:21.85 --> 00:01:26.59
been either concealed, deliberately erased,

00:01:26.59 --> 00:01:29.60
or ignored.

00:01:29.60 --> 00:01:36.94
And I feel that African-American history is American history.

00:01:36.94 --> 00:01:42.13
We contributed to this country just as much as anybody else.

00:01:42.13 --> 00:01:44.74
Butler perfects her craft at home in New Jersey,

00:01:44.74 --> 00:01:47.80
painstakingly choosing every fabric and stitch

00:01:47.80 --> 00:01:49.42
to bring her work to life.

00:01:49.42 --> 00:01:52.87
This one took how long, start to finish, to complete?

00:01:52.87 --> 00:01:54.82
This took a month.

00:01:54.82 --> 00:01:56.11
I love the hair.

00:01:56.11 --> 00:01:56.71
Thank you.

00:01:56.71 --> 00:01:58.33
I mean, I'm looking at lace.

00:01:58.33 --> 00:02:00.35
I would never see that as somebody's hair.

00:02:00.35 --> 00:02:04.12
Yeah, but I knew I wanted that because his Afro is always

00:02:04.12 --> 00:02:05.56
so well taken care of.

00:02:05.56 --> 00:02:07.15
You know about the Afro.

00:02:07.15 --> 00:02:09.76
It has to glisten.

00:02:09.76 --> 00:02:12.85
It took Butler 11 months to create her most recent quilt,

00:02:12.85 --> 00:02:15.55
commissioned by the Smithsonian, depicting the Harlem

00:02:15.55 --> 00:02:17.89
Hellfighters, an all Black infantry that

00:02:17.89 --> 00:02:19.48
fought in World War I.

00:02:19.48 --> 00:02:24.79
They were showing the world that they can be brave.

00:02:24.79 --> 00:02:28.74
That they are men, not boys.

00:02:28.74 --> 00:02:32.73
They hoped that if they fought valiantly in Europe,

00:02:32.73 --> 00:02:34.26
that when they came back to the US,

00:02:34.26 --> 00:02:36.13
they would be treated differently.

00:02:36.13 --> 00:02:37.29
They were not.

00:02:37.29 --> 00:02:39.09
A life mission stitching together

00:02:39.09 --> 00:02:42.87
the African-American experience, one portrait at a time.

00:02:42.87 --> 00:02:46.85
Maurice DuBois, CBS News, Newark, New Jersey.